cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on interference in mobile ad-hoc networks, which is a key topic in networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper analyzes the correlation of interference, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
3. cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) - The paper models the node locations as a Poisson point process, which is a common technique in multi-agent systems. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper analyzes the spatio-temporal aspects of wireless mobile systems, which can be viewed as a control problem. 
5. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper studies the correlation of interference and its impact on the performance of wireless mobile systems.
